{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775888897245,"sessionID":"ses_284c7642bffer8WIUavWmBu9rU","part":{"id":"prt_d7b38f84a001XqER3G0ImGFqWm","messageID":"msg_d7b38cd9d001qnWBznpEBKI87e","sessionID":"ses_284c7642bffer8WIUavWmBu9rU","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:2","state":{"status":"error","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","content":"# Proposal: AgentCube CLI Publish Command\n\n## AR-022 — CLI Publish Command\n\n| Attribute | Value |\n|-----------|-------|\n| **Module** | cmd/cli |\n| **Language** | Python |\n| **Size** | L |\n| **Status** | Proposed |\n\n---\n\n## 1. Purpose\n\nThe `publish` command is a critical component of the AgentCube CLI toolkit (`kubectl-agentcube`), enabling developers to deploy their packaged and built AI agents to Kubernetes environments. This command bridges the gap between local development and production deployment by providing a unified interface to publish agents to either:\n\n- **AgentCube Runtime**: Deploys an `AgentRuntime` Custom Resource (CR) to Kubernetes, leveraging the volcano.sh AgentCube ecosystem\n- **Standard Kubernetes**: Deploys traditional Kubernetes `Deployment` and `NodePort Service` resources for broader compatibility\n\nThe publish command completes the AI agent lifecycle management workflow: `pack` → `build` → `publish` → `invoke` → `status`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Scope\n\n### 2.1 In Scope\n\n#### Core Functionality\n- **Provider Selection**: Support for two deployment providers:\n  - `agentcube`: Deploys `AgentRuntime` CRs via `AgentCubeProvider`\n  - `k8s`: Deploys standard Kubernetes resources via `KubernetesProvider`\n\n- **Image Preparation**: \n  - Push locally built Docker images to configured registries\n  - Support for explicit image URLs (bypassing local Docker)\n  - Registry authentication via username/password\n\n- **AgentCube Provider Features**:\n  - Creation/patching of `AgentRuntime` CRs in the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group\n  - Automatic embedding of `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` and `ROUTER_URL` environment variables\n  - Configuration of session timeouts (`sessionTimeout: 15m`, `maxSessionDuration: 8h`)\n  - Integration with `imagePullSecrets` for private registries\n  - Readiness probe configuration support\n\n- **Kubernetes Provider Features**:\n  - Creation/patching of Kubernetes `Deployment` resources\n  - Creation/patching of `NodePort Service` resources\n  - Configurable replica counts\n  - Support for custom NodePort allocation (30000-32767 range)\n  - Deployment readiness waiting with configurable timeout (default 120s)\n\n#### Command Interface\n\n```\nkubectl-agentcube publish [OPTIONS]\n\nOptions:\n  -f, --workspace TEXT          Path to the agent workspace directory [default: .]\n  --version TEXT                Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0)\n  --image-url TEXT              Image repository URL (required in local build mode)\n  --image-username TEXT         Username for image repository\n  --image-password TEXT         Password for image repository\n  --description TEXT            Agent description\n  --region TEXT                 Deployment region\n  --cloud-provider TEXT         Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\n  --provider [agentcube|k8s]    Target provider [default: agentcube]\n  --node-port INTEGER           Specific NodePort to use (30000-32767) for K8s deployment\n  --replicas INTEGER            Number of replicas for K8s deployment [default: 1]\n  --namespace TEXT              The namespace for the deployment\n  --verbose                     Enable detailed logging\n```\n\n#### Metadata Integration\n- Read agent configuration from `agent_metadata.yaml` (with fallbacks to `agent.yaml`, `metadata.yaml`)\n- Merge CLI option overrides into metadata\n- Update metadata post-deployment with deployment information (`agent_id`, `k8s_deployment`, `agent_endpoint`)\n\n### 2.2 Out of Scope\n\n- **Build Functionality**: The publish command assumes the agent has already been built via the `build` command\n- **Packaging**: Workspace validation and Dockerfile generation remain in the `pack` command\n- **Invocation**: Direct agent testing remains in the `invoke` command\n- **Status Monitoring**: Long-term monitoring remains in the `status` command\n- **Multi-cloud Orchestration**: While cloud providers can be specified, cross-cloud deployment coordination is not implemented\n- **Automatic Rollback**: Failed deployments will report errors but will not automatically rollback\n\n---\n\n## 3. Impact Analysis\n\n### 3.1 System Components Affected\n\n| Component | Impact | Description |\n|-----------|--------|-------------|\n| `PublishRuntime` | New | Core runtime class implementing publish logic |\n| `AgentCubeProvider` | Enhanced | Adds `deploy_agent_runtime()` method for CR management |\n| `KubernetesProvider` | Enhanced | Adds `deploy_agent()`, `wait_for_deployment_ready()`, `delete_agent()` methods |\n| `DockerService` | Used | Leverages `push_image()` for registry operations |\n| `MetadataService` | Used | Reads/writes deployment info to metadata files |\n| `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Modified | Adds `publish` Typer command |\n| `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py` | Modified | Exports `PublishRuntime` |\n\n### 3.2 Dependencies\n\n#### Python Runtime Dependencies\n```toml\n[project]\ndependencies = [\n    \"typer[all]>=0.9.0\",\n    \"pydantic>=2.0.0\",\n    \"pyyaml>=6.0\",\n    \"httpx>=0.24.0\",\n    \"docker>=6.0.0\",\n    \"rich>=13.0.0\",\n    \"packaging>=23.0\",\n    \"importlib-resources>=6.0.0\",\n    \"semver>=3.0.0\",\n]\n\n[project.optional-dependencies]\nk8s = [\"kubernetes>=28.0.0\"]\n```\n\n#### External Dependencies\n- **Docker Daemon**: Required for local image builds and pushes\n- **Kubernetes Cluster**: Required for deployment (with appropriate kubeconfig)\n- **Container Registry**: Required for image hosting (e.g., Docker Hub, Huawei SWR)\n\n### 3.3 Kubernetes Permissions Required\n\n| Resource | Verbs | Purpose |\n|----------|-------|---------|\n| `namespaces` | get, create | Ensure target namespace exists |\n| `deployments` | get, create, patch, watch | Deploy and monitor agents (k8s provider) |\n| `services` | get, create, patch | Expose agents via NodePort (k8s provider) |\n| `agentruntimes` | get, create, patch | Deploy AgentRuntime CRs (agentcube provider) |\n| `secrets` | get, create | Manage image pull secrets |\n\n### 3.4 API Changes\n\n#### AgentRuntime CR Schema\n```yaml\napiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\nkind: AgentRuntime\nmetadata:\n  name: <agent-name>\n  namespace: <namespace>\nspec:\n  image: <image-url>\n  port: <port>\n  entrypoint: <entrypoint>\n  env:\n    - name: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\n      value: <url>\n    - name: ROUTER_URL\n      value: <url>\n  sessionTimeout: \"15m\"\n  maxSessionDuration: \"8h\"\n  imagePullSecrets:\n    - name: default-secret\n```\n\n### 3.5 Backward Compatibility\n\n- **Metadata Format**: New fields (`k8s_deployment`, `agent_endpoint`) are additive; existing metadata remains valid\n- **CLI Interface**: New command addition; no breaking changes to existing commands\n- **Provider Default**: Defaults to `agentcube` for consistency with ecosystem expectations\n\n### 3.6 Performance Considerations\n\n| Operation | Expected Duration | Notes |\n|-----------|-------------------|-------|\n| Image push | 30s - 5min | Depends on image size and network |\n| Deployment creation | 5-10s | API server response time |\n| Pod scheduling | 10-60s | Depends on cluster resources |\n| Readiness wait | Up to 120s | Configurable timeout |\n\n---\n\n## 4. Design Highlights\n\n### 4.1 PublishRuntime Architecture\n\n```python\nclass PublishRuntime:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n    def publish(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _publish_cr_to_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _publish_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _prepare_image_for_publishing(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n    def _prepare_local_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n    def _prepare_cloud_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n    def _update_publish_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, agent_info: Dict[str, Any]) -> None: ...\n```\n\n### 4.2 Provider Abstraction\n\nThe publish command uses a provider pattern to abstract deployment strategies:\n\n- **AgentCubeProvider**: Manages CR lifecycle for AgentCube ecosystem integration\n- **KubernetesProvider**: Manages native Kubernetes resources for standard deployments\n\nThis abstraction allows future providers (e.g., Helm, Terraform) to be added without modifying core publish logic.\n\n### 4.3 Error Handling\n\nAll errors are funneled through `_handle_error()`:\n- Non-verbose mode: Print error message in red, exit with code 1\n- Verbose mode: Print full traceback alongside error message\n\nSpecific error scenarios:\n- Missing AgentCube URLs: `ValueError` with clear guidance\n- Docker unavailable: `RuntimeError` before build attempt\n- Deployment timeout: `RuntimeError` after recording error in metadata\n- Invalid NodePort: Validation error (30000-32767 range)\n\n### 4.4 Metadata Persistence\n\nPost-publish metadata updates include:\n```yaml\nagent_id: <assigned-agent-id>\nk8s_deployment:\n  type: AgentRuntime | Deployment\n  name: <deployment-name>\n  namespace: <namespace>\n  node_port: <port>\n  replicas: <count>\nagent_endpoint: <invocation-url>\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. Alternatives Considered\n\n### 5.1 Alternative: Single Provider Model\n\n**Approach**: Only support AgentCube CR deployments, require users to use kubectl for standard Kubernetes.\n\n**Rejected**: Would limit CLI utility for users without AgentCube installed or those preferring standard Kubernetes patterns.\n\n### 5.2 Alternative: Helm Chart Deployment\n\n**Approach**: Generate and deploy Helm charts instead of raw Kubernetes resources.\n\n**Deferred**: Adds complexity and requires Helm installation. Can be added as a third provider in future iterations without breaking existing functionality.\n\n### 5.3 Alternative: GitOps Integration\n\n**Approach**: Push manifests to a Git repository for GitOps tooling (ArgoCD, Flux) to deploy.\n\n**Deferred**: Outside current scope but could be added as a `--strategy=gitops` option later.\n\n### 5.4 Alternative: Server-Side Build\n\n**Approach**: Send workspace to server for remote build and publish.\n\n**Rejected**: Increases server complexity and security exposure. Client-side build with push is more aligned with container best practices.\n\n### 5.5 Alternative: Implicit Image URL Detection\n\n**Approach**: Automatically detect image URL from metadata without explicit `--image-url` flag.\n\n**Partially Accepted**: Image URL is required for local build mode but optional if the image is already available in the registry. The explicit flag provides clarity and override capability.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Implementation Notes\n\n### 6.1 File Locations\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | `PublishRuntime` class implementation |\n| `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | AgentCube CR provider |\n| `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | Kubernetes native provider |\n| `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer command registration |\n\n### 6.2 Testing Strategy\n\n- Unit tests for `PublishRuntime` with mocked providers\n- Integration tests with fake Kubernetes clients\n- E2E tests requiring Docker and Kubernetes cluster (optional dependencies)\n\n### 6.3 Documentation Requirements\n\n- CLI help text (`--help` output)\n- User guide section on publishing agents\n- Troubleshooting guide for common deployment failures\n- Provider-specific configuration examples\n\n---\n\n## 7. Success Criteria\n\n1. **Functionality**: `kubectl-agentcube publish` successfully deploys agents to both AgentCube and standard Kubernetes\n2. **Integration**: Published agents can be invoked via `kubectl-agentcube invoke`\n3. **Idempotency**: Re-running publish updates existing deployments rather than failing\n4. **Observability**: Deployment status is visible via `kubectl-agentcube status`\n5. **Error Clarity**: All failure modes provide actionable error messages\n\n---\n\n## 8. Future Enhancements\n\n- Rolling update support with zero-downtime deployments\n- Blue-green deployment strategy option\n- Integration with cloud-specific container registries (ECR, ACR, GCR)\n- ConfigMap and Secret volume mounting\n- Horizontal Pod Autoscaler (HPA) configuration\n- Network policy generation\n\n---\n\n*This proposal is based on the AgentCube CLI Toolkit specification and Python SDK design documents.*\n"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775888897236,"end":1775888897242}}}}
