{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775889054492,"sessionID":"ses_284c7642bffer8WIUavWmBu9rU","part":{"id":"prt_d7b3a3c070015RwFNCcFMW2Rys","messageID":"msg_d7b3a2647001JgpLgfqYLHE4Ej","sessionID":"ses_284c7642bffer8WIUavWmBu9rU","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Proposal: CLI Publish Command (AR-022)\n\n## AR-022 — CLI Publish 命令\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Module** | `cmd/cli` |\n| **Language** | Python |\n| **Size** | L (Large) |\n| **Status** | Proposed |\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement the `publish` command for the AgentCube CLI to enable developers to deploy their packaged and built AI agents to Kubernetes environments. The publish command is the critical bridge between local development and production deployment, completing the agent lifecycle management workflow: `pack` → `build` → `publish` → `invoke` → `status`.\n\nThe publish command SHALL:\n- Deploy agents to Kubernetes using either AgentCube Custom Resources or standard Kubernetes resources\n- Support both local image pushes and explicit image URL references\n- Provide flexible provider selection (`agentcube` or `k8s`) for different deployment scenarios\n- Handle registry authentication and image preparation automatically\n- Update deployment metadata for subsequent `invoke` and `status` operations\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n1. **CLI Command Implementation**\n   - Add `publish` subcommand to the Typer CLI application\n   - Command options:\n     - `workspace` (`-f`, `--workspace`): Path to agent workspace directory (default: \".\")\n     - `version` (`--version`): Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0)\n     - `image_url` (`--image-url`): Image repository URL (required in local build mode)\n     - `image_username` (`--image-username`): Username for image repository\n     - `image_password` (`--image-password`): Password for image repository\n     - `description` (`--description`): Agent description\n     - `region` (`--region`): Deployment region\n     - `cloud_provider` (`--cloud-provider`): Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\n     - `provider` (`--provider`): Target provider - 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service) [default: \"agentcube\"]\n     - `node_port` (`--node-port`): Specific NodePort to use (30000-32767) for K8s deployment\n     - `replicas` (`--replicas`): Number of replicas for K8s deployment [default: 1]\n     - `namespace` (`--namespace`): The namespace for the deployment\n     - `verbose` (`--verbose`): Enable detailed logging\n\n2. **PublishRuntime Implementation**\n   - `PublishRuntime` class in `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n   - Core methods:\n     - `publish(workspace_path, **options)`: Main publish orchestration\n     - `_publish_cr_to_k8s()`: Deploy AgentRuntime CR via AgentCubeProvider\n     - `_publish_k8s()`: Deploy standard K8s resources via KubernetesProvider\n     - `_prepare_image_for_publishing()`: Prepare image (push or use explicit URL)\n     - `_prepare_local_image()`: Push locally built Docker images\n     - `_prepare_cloud_image()`: Handle cloud-built images\n     - `_update_publish_metadata()`: Persist deployment info to metadata\n\n3. **Provider Implementations**\n\n   **AgentCubeProvider** (`agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`):\n   - `deploy_agent_runtime()`: Create/patch AgentRuntime CR\n   - Automatic embedding of `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` and `ROUTER_URL` env vars\n   - Session timeout configuration (`sessionTimeout: 15m`, `maxSessionDuration: 8h`)\n   - Image pull secrets integration\n   - Readiness probe configuration\n\n   **KubernetesProvider** (`agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`):\n   - `deploy_agent()`: Create/patch Deployment and NodePort Service\n   - `wait_for_deployment_ready()`: Wait for rollout with timeout (default 120s)\n   - `get_agent_status()`: Retrieve deployment status\n   - `delete_agent()`: Clean up deployed resources\n\n4. **Image Management**\n   - Local Docker image push to registries with authentication\n   - Explicit image URL support for pre-pushed images\n   - Registry credential handling (username/password)\n   - Integration with `DockerService.push_image()`\n\n5. **Metadata Integration**\n   - Read agent configuration from `agent_metadata.yaml` (with fallbacks)\n   - Merge CLI option overrides into metadata\n   - Post-deployment metadata updates:\n     - `agent_id`: Assigned agent identifier\n     - `k8s_deployment`: Deployment details (type, name, namespace, node_port, replicas)\n     - `agent_endpoint`: Invocation URL\n\n6. **Error Handling**\n   - Missing AgentCube URLs validation with clear guidance\n   - Docker/registry authentication failures\n   - Kubernetes deployment failures with timeout handling\n   - Integration with `_handle_error()` for consistent CLI patterns\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n1. **Build Functionality**: Assumes image is already built via `build` command\n2. **Packaging**: Workspace validation remains in `pack` command\n3. **Direct Invocation**: Testing deployed agents handled by `invoke` command\n4. **Continuous Monitoring**: Long-term status tracking handled by `status` command\n5. **Multi-cloud Orchestration**: Cloud provider selection without cross-cloud coordination\n6. **Automatic Rollback**: Failed deployments report errors but don't auto-rollback\n7. **Helm Chart Deployment**: Raw Kubernetes resource management only\n8. **GitOps Integration**: Direct API server interaction only\n\n---\n\n## Design\n\n### Publish Command Flow\n\n```\npublish(workspace, options)\n    │\n    ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ Load Metadata               │\n│ - Read agent_metadata.yaml  │\n│ - Merge CLI overrides       │\n└─────────────┬───────────────┘\n              │\n              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ Validate Prerequisites      │\n│ - AgentCube URLs (if CR)    │\n│ - Image availability        │\n│ - K8s connectivity          │\n└─────────────┬───────────────┘\n              │\n              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ Prepare Image               │\n│ - Push local image OR       │\n│ - Use explicit image_url    │\n│ - Docker login if needed    │\n└─────────────┬───────────────┘\n              │\n              ├─ agentcube ─────► Deploy AgentRuntime CR\n              │                   - Apply CR to K8s\n              │                   - Wait for creation\n              │                   - Extract endpoint\n              │\n              └─ k8s ───────────► Deploy K8s Resources\n                                  - Create Deployment\n                                  - Create NodePort Service\n                                  - Wait for readiness (120s)\n                                  - Build service URL\n              │\n              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ Update Publish Metadata     │\n│ - Record deployment info    │\n│ - Save agent_metadata.yaml  │\n└─────────────┬───────────────┘\n              │\n              ▼\n         Return Result\n```\n\n### PublishRuntime Class Structure\n\n```python\nclass PublishRuntime:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n    \"\"\"Initialize with provider selection.\"\"\"\n    \n    def publish(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    \"\"\"Main entry point for publishing agents.\"\"\"\n    \n    def _publish_cr_to_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    \"\"\"Deploy AgentRuntime Custom Resource.\"\"\"\n    \n    def _publish_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    \"\"\"Deploy standard Kubernetes Deployment and Service.\"\"\"\n    \n    def _prepare_image_for_publishing(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n    \"\"\"Prepare image URL for deployment.\"\"\"\n    \n    def _prepare_local_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n    \"\"\"Push locally built Docker image to registry.\"\"\"\n    \n    def _prepare_cloud_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n    \"\"\"Handle cloud-built images.\"\"\"\n    \n    def _update_publish_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, agent_info: Dict[str, Any]) -> None: ...\n    \"\"\"Persist deployment information to metadata.\"\"\"\n```\n\n### AgentCubeProvider Deploy Flow\n\n```python\ndef deploy_agent_runtime(\n    self,\n    agent_name: str,\n    image_url: str,\n    port: int,\n    entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n    env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n    workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n    router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n    readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None,\n    readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None,\n) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"\n    1. Ensure namespace exists\n    2. Build AgentRuntime CR spec with:\n       - Image reference\n       - Environment variables (WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL, ROUTER_URL)\n       - Session timeouts (15m / 8h)\n       - Image pull secrets\n    3. Apply CR to cluster\n    4. Return deployment info\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n### KubernetesProvider Deploy Flow\n\n```python\ndef deploy_agent(\n    self,\n    agent_name: str,\n    image_url: str,\n    port: int,\n    entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n    replicas: int = 1,\n    node_port: Optional[int] = None,\n    env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"\n    1. Ensure namespace exists\n    2. Create/update Deployment\n    3. Create/update NodePort Service\n    4. Wait for deployment ready (timeout=120s)\n    5. Return deployment details including service_url\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Interface\n\n### Typer Publish Command Signature\n\n```python\ndef publish(\n    workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n    version: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--version\", help=\"Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0)\"),\n    image_url: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-url\", help=\"Image repository URL (required in local build mode)\"),\n    image_username: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-username\", help=\"Username for image repository\"),\n    image_password: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-password\", help=\"Password for image repository\"),\n    description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description\"),\n    region: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--region\", help=\"Deployment region\"),\n    cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--cloud-provider\", help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei)\"),\n    provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n    node_port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--node-port\", help=\"Specific NodePort to use (30000-32767) for K8s deployment\"),\n    replicas: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--replicas\", help=\"Number of replicas for K8s deployment (default: 1)\"),\n    namespace: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--namespace\", help=\"The namespace for the deployment\"),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n) -> None:\n```\n\n### Command Options Reference\n\n| Option | Short | Type | Default | Description |\n|--------|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--workspace` | `-f` | str | \".\" | Path to agent workspace directory |\n| `--version` | | str | None | Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0) |\n| `--image-url` | | str | None | Image repository URL (required in local build mode) |\n| `--image-username` | | str | None | Username for image repository |\n| `--image-password` | | str | None | Password for image repository |\n| `--description` | | str | None | Agent description |\n| `--region` | | str | None | Deployment region |\n| `--cloud-provider` | | str | None | Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei) |\n| `--provider` | | str | \"agentcube\" | Target provider: 'agentcube' or 'k8s' |\n| `--node-port` | | int | None | Specific NodePort (30000-32767) for K8s |\n| `--replicas` | | int | None | Number of replicas for K8s deployment |\n| `--namespace` | | str | None | Deployment namespace |\n| `--verbose` | | bool | False | Enable detailed logging |\n\n---\n\n## Implementation\n\n### Provider Selection Logic\n\n```python\ndef publish(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    provider_type = options.get('provider', 'agentcube')\n    metadata = self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n    \n    # Prepare image URL\n    image_url = self._prepare_image_for_publishing(workspace_path, metadata, options)\n    \n    if provider_type == 'agentcube':\n        # Validate AgentCube prerequisites\n        if not metadata.router_url or not metadata.workload_manager_url:\n            raise ValueError(\n                \"AgentCube provider requires router_url and workload_manager_url \"\n                \"in agent_metadata.yaml\"\n            )\n        return self._publish_cr_to_k8s(workspace_path, metadata, image_url=image_url, **options)\n    \n    elif provider_type == 'k8s':\n        return self._publish_k8s(workspace_path, metadata, image_url=image_url, **options)\n    \n    else:\n        raise ValueError(f\"Unknown provider: {provider_type}\")\n```\n\n### Image Preparation Logic\n\n```python\ndef _prepare_image_for_publishing(\n    self, \n    workspace_path: Path, \n    metadata, \n    options: Dict[str, Any]\n) -> str:\n    \"\"\"\n    Prepare image URL for deployment:\n    1. If image_url provided in options, use it directly\n    2. If build_mode is 'local', push local image to registry\n    3. If build_mode is 'cloud', use cloud-built image URL\n    \"\"\"\n    if options.get('image_url'):\n        return options['image_url']\n    \n    if metadata.build_mode == 'local':\n        return self._prepare_local_image(workspace_path, metadata, options)\n    else:\n        return self._prepare_cloud_image(workspace_path, metadata, options)\n\ndef _prepare_local_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Push local Docker image to configured registry.\"\"\"\n    image_name = metadata.agent_name\n    tag = metadata.version or \"latest\"\n    \n    # Construct full image URL with registry\n    registry_url = options.get('image_url') or metadata.registry_url\n    if registry_url:\n        full_image_name = f\"{registry_url}/{image_name}:{tag}\"\n    else:\n        full_image_name = f\"{image_name}:{tag}\"\n    \n    # Push image with authentication if provided\n    self.docker_service.push_image(\n        image_name=image_name,\n        registry_url=registry_url,\n        username=options.get('image_username') or metadata.registry_username,\n        password=options.get('image_password') or metadata.registry_password,\n    )\n    \n    return full_image_name\n```\n\n### AgentCube CR Deployment\n\n```python\ndef _publish_cr_to_k8s(\n    self, \n    workspace_path: Path, \n    metadata, \n    image_url: str,\n    **options: Any\n) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Deploy AgentRuntime Custom Resource.\"\"\"\n    \n    provider = AgentCubeProvider(\n        namespace=options.get('namespace', 'default'),\n        verbose=self.verbose\n    )\n    \n    result = provider.deploy_agent_runtime(\n        agent_name=metadata.agent_name,\n        image_url=image_url,\n        port=metadata.port,\n        entrypoint=metadata.entrypoint,\n        workload_manager_url=metadata.workload_manager_url,\n        router_url=metadata.router_url,\n        readiness_probe_path=metadata.readiness_probe_path,\n        readiness_probe_port=metadata.readiness_probe_port,\n    )\n    \n    # Update metadata with deployment info\n    agent_info = {\n        \"agent_id\": result.get(\"agent_id\"),\n        \"agent_endpoint\": result.get(\"agent_endpoint\"),\n        \"k8s_deployment\": {\n            \"type\": \"AgentRuntime\",\n            \"name\": result.get(\"name\"),\n            \"namespace\": result.get(\"namespace\"),\n        }\n    }\n    self._update_publish_metadata(workspace_path, agent_info)\n    \n    return result\n```\n\n### Kubernetes Native Deployment\n\n```python\ndef _publish_k8s(\n    self, \n    workspace_path: Path, \n    metadata, \n    image_url: str,\n    **options: Any\n) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Deploy standard Kubernetes resources.\"\"\"\n    \n    provider = KubernetesProvider(\n        namespace=options.get('namespace', 'default'),\n        verbose=self.verbose\n    )\n    \n    result = provider.deploy_agent(\n        agent_name=metadata.agent_name,\n        image_url=image_url,\n        port=metadata.port,\n        entrypoint=metadata.entrypoint,\n        replicas=options.get('replicas', 1),\n        node_port=options.get('node_port'),\n    )\n    \n    # Wait for deployment to be ready\n    try:\n        provider.wait_for_deployment_ready(\n            name=result['deployment_name'],\n            timeout=120\n        )\n        result['status'] = 'ready'\n    except TimeoutError:\n        result['status'] = 'timeout'\n        raise RuntimeError(f\"Deployment timed out after 120s\")\n    \n    # Update metadata with deployment info\n    agent_info = {\n        \"agent_endpoint\": result.get('service_url'),\n        \"k8s_deployment\": {\n            \"type\": \"Deployment\",\n            \"name\": result.get('deployment_name'),\n            \"namespace\": result.get('namespace'),\n            \"node_port\": result.get('node_port'),\n            \"replicas\": result.get('replicas'),\n        }\n    }\n    self._update_publish_metadata(workspace_path, agent_info)\n    \n    return result\n```\n\n### Error Handling Pattern\n\nAll publish errors SHALL propagate through `_handle_error()`:\n- Non-verbose: Print concise error message in red\n- Verbose: Print full traceback\n- Exit code: 1 on any publish failure\n\n**Specific Error Cases:**\n\n| Error | Condition | Handling |\n|-------|-----------|----------|\n| `ValueError` | Missing AgentCube URLs | \"router_url and workload_manager_url required in agent_metadata.yaml\" |\n| `ValueError` | Invalid NodePort | \"NodePort must be in range 30000-32767\" |\n| `RuntimeError` | Docker push failure | Clear error with registry details |\n| `TimeoutError` | K8s deployment timeout | \"Deployment timed out after 120s\" |\n| `RuntimeError` | K8s API errors | Include server error message |\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Affected Components\n\n| Component | Impact Level | Description |\n|-----------|--------------|-------------|\n| `agentcube/cli/main.py` | High | New `publish` command registration and option handling |\n| `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | High | New runtime class implementation (~250 lines) |\n| `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py` | Medium | Export `PublishRuntime` class |\n| `agentcube/__init__.py` | Low | Add `PublishRuntime` to exports |\n| `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | High | New provider for AgentRuntime CR management |\n| `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | High | New provider for K8s native resources |\n| `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | Medium | Use `push_image()` for registry operations |\n| `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Low | Metadata read/write for deployment tracking |\n\n### Dependencies\n\n**Required:**\n- `pack` and `build` commands must be executed before `publish` (validated via metadata)\n- `DockerService` for local image pushes\n- `AgentMetadata` model for configuration and deployment tracking\n- Kubernetes cluster access (kubeconfig) for deployment\n\n**Dependent:**\n- `invoke` command depends on successful `publish` output (agent_endpoint)\n- `status` command depends on publish metadata (k8s_deployment info)\n\n### Kubernetes RBAC Requirements\n\n| Resource | Verbs | Purpose |\n|----------|-------|---------|\n| `namespaces` | get, create | Ensure target namespace exists |\n| `deployments` | get, create, patch, watch | Deploy and monitor agents (k8s provider) |\n| `services` | get, create, patch | Expose agents via NodePort (k8s provider) |\n| `agentruntimes` | get, create, patch | Deploy AgentRuntime CRs (agentcube provider) |\n| `secrets` | get, create | Manage image pull secrets |\n\n### Risk Assessment\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|--------|------------|\n| K8s cluster unavailable | Medium | High | Clear error message; validate connectivity early |\n| Registry authentication failure | Medium | High | Test credentials before push; clear error messages |\n| Image push network issues | Medium | Medium | Retry logic; document troubleshooting steps |\n| K8s deployment scheduling failures | Low | High | Wait with timeout; provide debugging commands |\n| Invalid NodePort conflicts | Low | Medium | Validate range; auto-assign if not specified |\n| CRD not installed (AgentCube) | Medium | High | Check CRD presence; provide install instructions |\n\n### Performance Characteristics\n\n| Operation | Time (est.) | Notes |\n|-----------|-------------|-------|\n| `publish` (image push) | 30s - 5min | Depends on image size and network |\n| `publish` (CR creation) | 5-10s | API server response time |\n| `publish` (K8s deployment) | 30-180s | Includes pod scheduling and readiness |\n| Docker login | 1-3s | Registry authentication |\n| Metadata update | <100ms | YAML serialization |\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Single Provider Model\n\n**Approach**: Only support AgentCube CR deployments, require users to use kubectl for standard Kubernetes.\n\n**Rejected**: Would limit CLI utility for users without AgentCube installed or those preferring standard Kubernetes patterns. The dual-provider approach maximizes flexibility.\n\n### Alternative 2: Helm Chart Deployment\n\n**Approach**: Generate and deploy Helm charts instead of raw Kubernetes resources.\n\n**Deferred**: Adds complexity and requires Helm installation. Can be added as a third provider (`--provider=helm`) in future iterations without breaking existing functionality.\n\n### Alternative 3: GitOps Integration\n\n**Approach**: Push manifests to a Git repository for GitOps tooling (ArgoCD, Flux) to deploy.\n\n**Deferred**: Outside current scope but could be added as a `--strategy=gitops` option later.\n\n### Alternative 4: Implicit Provider Selection\n\n**Approach**: Automatically detect whether to use AgentCube or standard K8s based on cluster capabilities.\n\n**Rejected**: Explicit provider selection is clearer and avoids surprising behavior. Users should consciously choose their deployment target.\n\n### Alternative 5: Server-Side Image Build\n\n**Approach**: Push workspace to server for remote build and publish in one step.\n\n**Rejected**: Increases server complexity and security exposure. Client-side build with separate publish step is more aligned with container best practices and gives users more control.\n\n### Alternative 6: Automatic Port Allocation\n\n**Approach**: Always auto-assign NodePort instead of allowing explicit specification.\n\n**Partially Accepted**: Auto-allocation is the default, but explicit `--node-port` is supported for users who need predictable ports for firewall rules or documentation.\n\n---\n\n## Verification\n\n### Publish Command Verification (AgentCube Provider)\n\n```bash\n# Prerequisites: pack and build commands executed\nkubectl-agentcube pack -f /tmp/test-agent --agent-name test-agent\nkubectl-agentcube build -f /tmp/test-agent\n\n# Configure AgentCube URLs\ncat >> /tmp/test-agent/agent_metadata.yaml << EOF\nrouter_url: http://router.agentcube.svc.cluster.local:8080\nworkload_manager_url: http://workload-manager.agentcube.svc.cluster.local:8080\nEOF\n\n# Publish with AgentCube provider\nkubectl-agentcube publish -f /tmp/test-agent \\\n  --provider agentcube \\\n  --namespace default \\\n  --verbose\n\n# Verify AgentRuntime CR was created\nkubectl get agentruntimes -n default\n\n# Verify metadata was updated\nkubectl-agentcube status -f /tmp/test-agent --provider agentcube\n```\n\n### Publish Command Verification (K8s Provider)\n\n```bash\n# Prerequisites: pack and build commands executed\nkubectl-agentcube pack -f /tmp/test-agent --agent-name test-agent\nkubectl-agentcube build -f /tmp/test-agent\n\n# Publish with K8s provider\nkubectl-agentcube publish -f /tmp/test-agent \\\n  --provider k8s \\\n  --namespace default \\\n  --replicas 2 \\\n  --node-port 30080 \\\n  --verbose\n\n# Verify Deployment and Service were created\nkubectl get deployment,service -n default -l app=test-agent\n\n# Verify endpoint is accessible\ncurl http://localhost:30080/health\n\n# Verify metadata was updated\ncat /tmp/test-agent/agent_metadata.yaml | grep -A10 \"k8s_deployment\"\n```\n\n### Registry Authentication Verification\n\n```bash\n# Publish with registry credentials\nkubectl-agentcube publish -f /tmp/test-agent \\\n  --image-url registry.example.com/agents/test-agent \\\n  --image-username $REGISTRY_USER \\\n  --image-password $REGISTRY_PASS \\\n  --verbose\n```\n\n### Error Handling Verification\n\n```bash\n# Test missing AgentCube URLs\nkubectl-agentcube publish -f /tmp/test-agent --provider agentcube 2>&1 | grep -q \"router_url\" && echo \"Validation works\"\n\n# Test invalid NodePort\nkubectl-agentcube publish -f /tmp/test-agent --provider k8s --node-port 99999 2>&1 | grep -q \"30000-32767\" && echo \"Port validation works\"\n\n# Test verbose mode\nkubectl-agentcube publish -f /tmp/test-agent --verbose 2>&1 | grep -q \"Publishing\" && echo \"Verbose mode works\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- [cli-toolkit/design.md](cli-toolkit/design.md) — Detailed CLI design specifications\n- [cli-toolkit/spec.md](cli-toolkit/spec.md) — Complete requirements specification\n- [deployment/client-go.md](deployment/client-go.md) — client-go library for AgentRuntime CR\n- AR-020 — CLI Pack Command — Predecessor in lifecycle\n- AR-021 — CLI Build Command — Predecessor in lifecycle\n- AR-023 — CLI Invoke Command — Successor in lifecycle\n- AR-024 — CLI Status Command — Successor in lifecycle\n\n---\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n1. ✅ `publish` command is registered in Typer CLI with all specified options\n2. ✅ `PublishRuntime` class implements all required methods per spec\n3. ✅ AgentCube provider (`agentcube`) deploys `AgentRuntime` CRs successfully\n4. ✅ Kubernetes provider (`k8s`) deploys Deployment and NodePort Service successfully\n5. ✅ Image push works with `DockerService.push_image()` and registry authentication\n6. ✅ Explicit `image_url` bypasses local Docker push\n7. ✅ Missing AgentCube URLs produce clear error: \"router_url and workload_manager_url required\"\n8. ✅ Deployment metadata is persisted to `agent_metadata.yaml` (agent_id, k8s_deployment, agent_endpoint)\n9. ✅ K8s deployment waits for readiness with 120s timeout\n10. ✅ NodePort validation ensures range 30000-32767\n11. ✅ All errors use consistent `_handle_error()` pattern with exit code 1\n12. ✅ Verbose mode enables DEBUG logging and full tracebacks\n13. ✅ Command integrates with existing CLI structure and styling\n14. ✅ Published agents can be invoked via `kubectl-agentcube invoke`\n15. ✅ Published agent status is visible via `kubectl-agentcube status`\n\n---\n\n*AR-022 — Module: cmd/cli — Language: Python — Size: L*\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775889054377,"end":1775889054488}}}}
