{"type":"text","timestamp":1775889072190,"sessionID":"ses_284c7642bffer8WIUavWmBu9rU","part":{"id":"prt_d7b3ca362001Yzt3hqDZaUI1tv","messageID":"msg_d7b3c7b5c001NCREIlzf272Dxn","sessionID":"ses_284c7642bffer8WIUavWmBu9rU","type":"text","text":"I've written the `proposal.md` file for **AR-022 — CLI Publish Command**. The proposal covers:\n\n## Summary\n\n| Section | Content |\n|---------|---------|\n| **Purpose** | Deploys packaged/built agents to Kubernetes via AgentCube CR or standard K8s resources |\n| **Scope** | PublishRuntime, AgentCubeProvider, KubernetesProvider, image push, metadata updates |\n| **Design** | Command flow, class structure, provider deployment flows |\n| **Interface** | Complete Typer command signature with 14 options |\n| **Implementation** | Provider selection, image preparation, CR/K8s deployment, error handling |\n| **Impact Analysis** | 8 affected components, K8s RBAC requirements, risk assessment |\n| **Alternatives** | 6 alternatives considered (single provider, Helm, GitOps, etc.) |\n| **Verification** | Test commands for both providers, registry auth, error handling |\n| **Success Criteria** | 15 specific verification criteria |\n\n## Key Features Covered\n\n- **Dual Provider Support**: `agentcube` (AgentRuntime CR) and `k8s` (Deployment + NodePort Service)\n- **Image Management**: Local Docker push with auth + explicit image URL support\n- **AgentCube Integration**: CR deployment with workload_manager_url, router_url, session timeouts\n- **K8s Native**: Deployment readiness waiting (120s timeout), configurable replicas, NodePort allocation\n- **Metadata Updates**: Records agent_id, k8s_deployment, agent_endpoint for invoke/status commands","time":{"start":1775889072188,"end":1775889072188}}}
